Definition.WordDefinition:
Tubing \Tub"ing\, n. 1. The act of making tubes. [1913 Webster]
2. A series of tubes; tubes, collectively; a length or piece of a tube; material for tubes; as, leather tubing. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Tube \Tube\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Tubed}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Tubing}.] To furnish with a tube; as, to tube a well. [1913 Webster]
tubing n : conduit consisting of a long hollow object (usually cylindrical) used to hold and conduct objects or liquids or gases [syn: {tube}]
